Mom?

550
00:30:39,672 --> 00:30:40,589
Here, Honey!

551
00:30:40,589 --> 00:30:42,133
Mommy!

552
00:30:42,383 --> 00:30:43,634
Hi!

553
00:30:45,636 --> 00:30:46,429
I’ll do it.

554
00:30:46,429 --> 00:30:47,822
- Hi, Honey!
- Thank you.

555
00:30:47,847 --> 00:30:48,806
Hi!

556
00:30:48,806 --> 00:30:49,598
Thank you so much.

557
00:30:49,598 --> 00:30:50,499
We have a guest.

558
00:30:50,773 --> 00:30:52,024
Is she Alys?

559
00:30:52,049 --> 00:30:55,438
I’m Alys Zyril Perez.
Nice to meet you, Madam.

560
00:30:56,063 --> 00:30:57,606
Nice to meet you, too, dear.

561
00:30:57,606 --> 00:30:58,648
Please sit down.

562
00:30:58,771 --> 00:30:59,968
Let's go, let's go.

563
00:31:07,509 --> 00:31:09,041
What are your credentials?

564
00:31:09,869 --> 00:31:10,703
Oh!

565
00:31:11,120 --> 00:31:13,914
I initially studied Advertising in NYCU but

566
00:31:13,914 --> 00:31:17,209
I had to stop to pursue my real passion.

567
00:31:17,626 --> 00:31:20,588
So, I studied in Paris
to take Culinary Arts

568
00:31:20,588 --> 00:31:22,798
Major in Pastry and Baking.

569
00:31:23,799 --> 00:31:24,592
<i>Wait,</i>

570
00:31:24,592 --> 00:31:26,135
<i>is this a job interview?</i>

571
00:31:26,135 --> 00:31:27,178
<i>I thought</i>

572
00:31:27,178 --> 00:31:28,387
<i>this was a taste test,</i>

573
00:31:28,387 --> 00:31:30,014
<i>and then we'll sign the deal?</i>

574
00:31:30,668 --> 00:31:31,961
Impressive.

575
00:31:33,142 --> 00:31:35,519
My daughter finished her
undergrad at St. Collete's.

576
00:31:35,770 --> 00:31:38,898
And had her MBAs at Harvard.

577
00:31:42,151 --> 00:31:43,152
Hi, Auntie!

578
00:31:43,152 --> 00:31:45,877
Drake! You're here!

579
00:31:47,447 --> 00:31:49,533
- How are you?
- Baby Ethos, come here!

580
00:31:49,533 --> 00:31:50,493
I’m okay.

581
00:31:50,785 --> 00:31:51,619
How are you?

582
00:31:51,619 --> 00:31:53,662
I'm doing fine.
A little tired from Ethos.

583
00:31:53,662 --> 00:31:54,997
Oh, okay.

584
00:31:54,997 --> 00:31:55,998
Looking good.

585
00:31:55,998 --> 00:31:56,916
Thank you, Auntie.

586
00:31:56,916 --> 00:31:57,917
I missed you.

587
00:31:58,000 --> 00:31:59,835
- Nice to see you.
- Nice to see you again.

588
00:31:59,835 --> 00:32:01,879
I think my mom has a crush on Drake.

589
00:32:01,879 --> 00:32:04,089
She's mad at me for marrying him.

590
00:32:05,445 --> 00:32:08,615
Baby Ethos, I missed you!
Did you miss me?

591
00:32:08,928 --> 00:32:10,179
Okay, kiss!

592
00:32:11,096 --> 00:32:12,786
Okay, kiss Godmother Alys too!

593
00:32:13,439 --> 00:32:14,286
No!

594
00:32:15,017 --> 00:32:15,904
No?

595
00:32:17,910 --> 00:32:19,205
Ethos, you want? Cakes?

596
00:32:19,230 --> 00:32:20,130
No!

597
00:32:23,025 --> 00:32:26,670
<i>Okay, Alys. He’s just a kid, okay?</i>

598
00:32:26,695 --> 00:32:29,365
<i>Don’t take it personal.</i>
<i>He is Tripp’s cousin.</i>

599
00:32:35,913 --> 00:32:37,206
Okay!

600
00:32:37,498 --> 00:32:39,166
Okay, you sit here, okay?

601
00:32:39,416 --> 00:32:41,335
Just play with your helicopter, okay?

602
00:32:41,752 --> 00:32:42,795
Just stay safe.

603
00:32:43,170 --> 00:32:44,021
Okay?

604
00:32:44,380 --> 00:32:45,798
Drake, I told you!

605
00:32:45,969 --> 00:32:47,201
Beach wedding!

606
00:32:47,364 --> 00:32:49,497
Alys said she likes beach wedding, too!

607
00:32:51,053 --> 00:32:51,911
Okay.

608
00:32:52,395 --> 00:32:53,438
Yay!

609
00:32:53,463 --> 00:32:54,255
Okay!

610
00:32:54,674 --> 00:32:56,384
And about the wedding dress,

611
00:32:56,517 --> 00:32:57,388
Palma,

612
00:32:57,684 --> 00:32:58,727
I'll change it, okay?

613
00:33:00,042 --> 00:33:00,876
Okay.

614
00:33:01,647 --> 00:33:02,857
Oh wait, Alys,

615
00:33:03,271 --> 00:33:04,567
I forgot to tell you.

616
00:33:06,355 --> 00:33:07,523
We have a problem.

617
00:33:08,237 --> 00:33:10,447
So, our wedding planner

618
00:33:10,447 --> 00:33:11,824
scammed us.

619
00:33:12,283 --> 00:33:15,310
He cancelled and since

620
00:33:15,661 --> 00:33:17,788
you're hands on with the preps and...

621
00:33:18,414 --> 00:33:19,915
you're friends with Drake,

622
00:33:20,499 --> 00:33:22,459
can you please step up for us?

623
00:33:22,459 --> 00:33:23,460
Please!

624
00:33:28,757 --> 00:33:29,815
Uh...

625
00:33:30,217 --> 00:33:31,010
Uhm...

626
00:33:31,010 --> 00:33:33,220
Great! Okay!
Silence means yes!

627
00:33:33,220 --> 00:33:35,014
Thank you so much, Alys!

628
00:33:36,181 --> 00:33:37,391
You're really my savior!

629
00:33:37,391 --> 00:33:38,934
Thank you, thank you so much, Alys!

630
00:33:39,727 --> 00:33:41,270
Oh, Ethos!

631
00:33:41,270 --> 00:33:42,062
My baby!

632
00:33:42,062 --> 00:33:43,647
I have so many lollipops in my room.

633
00:33:43,672 --> 00:33:46,216
<i>Wait, why is this
happening all of a sudden?</i>

634
00:33:48,569 --> 00:33:49,494
I'm done.

635
00:33:50,446 --> 00:33:51,697
I'm leaving.

636
00:33:56,327 --> 00:33:57,268
What?

637
00:33:59,181 --> 00:34:00,557
Are you going to the reunion?

638
00:34:02,833 --> 00:34:04,418
Tripp invited me.

639
00:34:06,093 --> 00:34:07,178
Don't go, Alys.

640
00:34:09,663 --> 00:34:10,580
Please.

641
00:34:10,605 --> 00:34:12,023
Don't go.

642
00:34:15,638 --> 00:34:16,838
Why, Drake?

643
00:34:17,181 --> 00:34:19,099
Give me one good reason.

644
00:34:20,059 --> 00:34:21,101
Because...

645
00:34:24,613 --> 00:34:26,807
Because the next time
you see the Palmas,

646
00:34:27,900 --> 00:34:29,652
I'll introduce you as my wife.

647
00:34:30,037 --> 00:34:33,499
You'll only confuse my
family as Tripp's girlfriend

648
00:34:33,799 --> 00:34:35,383
but my future wife after.

649
00:34:36,241 --> 00:34:37,826
Please, Alys. Don't go.

650
00:34:57,805 --> 00:35:00,808
As far as I'm concerned,
I'm not a wedding planner.

651
00:35:00,808 --> 00:35:03,852
But why the hell am I
planning Drake's wedding?

652
00:35:04,478 --> 00:35:06,563
My god. How did they get me
to agree to this?

653
00:35:07,113 --> 00:35:11,200
Did I feel bad for them because their
wedding planner cancelled last minute?

654
00:35:12,236 --> 00:35:13,529
Oh my god, Alys.

655
00:35:13,529 --> 00:35:15,572
What did you get yourself into?

656
00:35:18,826 --> 00:35:19,952
- You're here!
- Silly!

657
00:35:19,952 --> 00:35:21,773
What's with the long face?

658
00:35:21,912 --> 00:35:24,081
Hi, Silly!
Have you been here long?

659
00:35:24,623 --> 00:35:26,792
I'm sorry, Silly.

660
00:35:27,164 --> 00:35:29,381
It's all Cristine's fault!

661
00:35:31,505 --> 00:35:32,881
You could cancel.

662
00:35:34,299 --> 00:35:36,218
Cancelling is not an option.

663
00:35:37,094 --> 00:35:38,429
This is important to me.

664
00:35:38,429 --> 00:35:40,390
And plus she's super nice.

665
00:35:40,639 --> 00:35:42,099
As for her mom,

666
00:35:42,599 --> 00:35:44,393
she gave me a huge job.

667
00:35:44,393 --> 00:35:46,729
I'll be serving pastries
in her art galleries,

668
00:35:46,729 --> 00:35:48,022
and it's one of the finest.

669
00:35:48,022 --> 00:35:49,648
So this will be my biggest break.

670
00:35:51,358 --> 00:35:52,265
That's great.

671
00:35:53,152 --> 00:35:53,944
But...

672
00:35:55,070 --> 00:35:56,947
If it's taking a toll on you,

673
00:35:57,781 --> 00:35:59,324
you can always say no.

674
00:36:00,743 --> 00:36:01,882
Not really.

675
00:36:02,077 --> 00:36:04,367
I think I'm just overwhelmed.

676
00:36:07,916 --> 00:36:08,792
Okay!

677
00:36:08,792 --> 00:36:10,586
I think I'm done for today.

678
00:36:15,382 --> 00:36:16,550
Mushy much?

679
00:36:18,677 --> 00:36:20,220
You're just so busy now, Perez.

680
00:36:20,795 --> 00:36:22,339
You don't have time for me anymore.

681
00:36:23,364 --> 00:36:25,741
Well, that's why we have dinner later.

682
00:36:28,270 --> 00:36:29,461
Unfortunately,

683
00:36:29,565 --> 00:36:30,640
Tofer's coming.

684
00:36:32,840 --> 00:36:34,418
Why are we taking Tofer?

685
00:36:34,443 --> 00:36:36,028
Your cousin really misses you!

686
00:36:36,028 --> 00:36:38,530
Take some responsibility, Marco!

687
00:36:40,032 --> 00:36:40,824
Come on.

688
00:36:40,824 --> 00:36:43,164
You're his favorite cousin, right?

689
00:36:43,577 --> 00:36:44,570
Play nice.

690
00:36:47,581 --> 00:36:48,578
Okay.

691
00:36:49,355 --> 00:36:50,312
Fine, Silly.

692
00:36:52,419 --> 00:36:53,378
I love you, Silly.

693
00:36:54,129 --> 00:36:55,148
I love you, too.

694
00:37:02,304 --> 00:37:04,264
What?! No!

695
00:37:04,264 --> 00:37:06,391
Don't send them a freakin' notice!

696
00:37:06,391 --> 00:37:08,268
I'll arrange for that!

697
00:37:08,268 --> 00:37:09,353
You got that?!

698
00:37:09,353 --> 00:37:10,312
Copy?

699
00:37:12,147 --> 00:37:12,981
Good.

700
00:37:13,006 --> 00:37:14,007
Oh, geez!

701
00:37:17,069 --> 00:37:19,613
You should really control
your caffeine intake!

702
00:37:20,072 --> 00:37:21,156
It's too much.

703
00:37:21,448 --> 00:37:23,033
How long were you standing there?

704
00:37:23,408 --> 00:37:26,578
Just long enough for me to hear
your supposed assault.

705
00:37:26,578 --> 00:37:28,247
Who is that, anyway?

706
00:37:28,705 --> 00:37:29,820
Stalker.

707
00:37:30,916 --> 00:37:32,084
Disgusting.

708
00:37:32,918 --> 00:37:34,169
Not my type at all.

709
00:37:34,169 --> 00:37:34,920
Really?

710
00:37:34,920 --> 00:37:35,875
You sure?

711
00:37:37,089 --> 00:37:38,006
Tripp!

712
00:37:39,591 --> 00:37:40,843
Geez!

713
00:37:41,135 --> 00:37:42,678
You’re hugging me too much!

714
00:37:42,928 --> 00:37:43,953
Oh, man.

715
00:37:44,179 --> 00:37:45,806
Are your sure that hug is for me?

716
00:37:47,683 --> 00:37:48,809
You don't have to be mean.

717
00:37:49,810 --> 00:37:51,854
You guys are really a couple.

718
00:37:52,521 --> 00:37:55,274
Hey, I'm not as mean as you!

719
00:37:56,108 --> 00:37:57,776
So? Let's go!

720
00:37:57,776 --> 00:37:58,819
I'm starving.

721
00:37:58,819 --> 00:37:59,403
Come on.

722
00:37:59,403 --> 00:38:01,113
Let's go!

723
00:38:02,865 --> 00:38:04,283
Who’s the couple now?

724
00:38:04,283 --> 00:38:05,701
You left me behind!

725
00:38:05,784 --> 00:38:06,869
So annoying!

726
00:38:07,286 --> 00:38:08,370
Hey!

727
00:38:11,582 --> 00:38:13,083
Ma’am, here are your slippers.

728
00:38:14,042 --> 00:38:15,377
Thank you, Manang.

729
00:38:23,844 --> 00:38:24,595
Hello?

730
00:38:24,595 --> 00:38:25,726
Alys?

731
00:38:26,054 --> 00:38:28,015
Sorry to bother you with this.

732
00:38:28,557 --> 00:38:30,767
But I'll be going to
Paris for a convention.

733
00:38:31,602 --> 00:38:34,271
<i>And I won't be back until</i>
<i>the day of my marriage.</i>

734
00:38:35,063 --> 00:38:36,956
<i>Please coordinate with Drake instead.</i>

735
00:38:37,816 --> 00:38:38,855
Wait.

736
00:38:38,942 --> 00:38:39,925
Hold on.

737
00:38:40,110 --> 00:38:41,778
Am I hearing this right?

738
00:38:42,446 --> 00:38:45,699
You're leaving then coming back
on the day of your wedding?

739
00:38:46,186 --> 00:38:48,188
I'm sorry for this. Really!

740
00:38:48,368 --> 00:38:50,287
But this is really important.

741
00:38:51,031 --> 00:38:52,283
<i>Is she mental?!</i>

742
00:38:52,664 --> 00:38:55,675
<i>She's leaving then coming back</i>
<i>for the wedding itself?</i>

743
00:38:56,910 --> 00:38:58,787
Wait, can't we just...

744
00:38:59,046 --> 00:39:00,547
you know, push the wedding back?

745
00:39:00,672 --> 00:39:02,049
This is a big deal, Cristine.

746
00:39:02,049 --> 00:39:03,425
You have to be here!

747
00:39:03,518 --> 00:39:04,936
Oh, no, no...

748
00:39:04,961 --> 00:39:06,421
The date will be the same.

749
00:39:06,568 --> 00:39:08,404
<i>I'll just be gone for a bit, Alys.</i>

750
00:39:09,075 --> 00:39:10,368
<i>You could still call me.</i>

751
00:39:10,704 --> 00:39:13,370
It's just my physical presence
won't be there anymore.

752
00:39:14,269 --> 00:39:16,271
Please coordinate with Drake instead.

753
00:39:17,272 --> 00:39:18,690
Thanks a lot, Alys.

754
00:39:18,690 --> 00:39:20,150
And I really have to go now.

755
00:39:20,525 --> 00:39:21,534
Bye!

756
00:39:23,695 --> 00:39:25,322
She just hung up on me!

757
00:39:34,957 --> 00:39:36,250
<i>Cristine's gone.</i>

758
00:39:36,250 --> 00:39:38,710
<i>It's you and me again, Alys.</i>

759
00:39:38,710 --> 00:39:40,420
<i>Hello, pseudo bride.</i>

760
00:39:40,420 --> 00:39:41,964
<i>Make your groom happy.</i>

761
00:39:41,964 --> 00:39:43,081
<i>You ready?</i>

762
00:39:45,408 --> 00:39:46,409
What the f —

763
00:39:50,451 --> 00:39:52,619
<i>SOS!!!</i>

764
00:39:59,940 --> 00:40:00,816
Oh!

765
00:40:00,816 --> 00:40:02,359
I thought this was an S.O.S?

766
00:40:03,318 --> 00:40:05,433
Which market are you going to, Perez?

767
00:40:06,238 --> 00:40:07,572
What are you wearing?

768
00:40:07,948 --> 00:40:09,658
Why?
What's wrong with this?

769
00:40:09,658 --> 00:40:11,743
I'm wearing crop top and shorts!

770
00:40:11,743 --> 00:40:13,620
Is that what being on the market is?

771
00:40:14,329 --> 00:40:16,120
Well, you don’t know
anything about fashion.

772
00:40:16,159 --> 00:40:16,892
You’re so annoying.

773
00:40:16,917 --> 00:40:17,499
Get over it.

774
00:40:17,545 --> 00:40:18,963
So much for fashion—it looks cheap.

775
00:40:20,377 --> 00:40:21,670
Cheap my ass!

776
00:40:36,351 --> 00:40:37,728
What is it now?

777
00:40:38,228 --> 00:40:41,293
Gosh, your car smells good.
It smells like strawberries.

778
00:40:41,565 --> 00:40:42,232
Of course.

779
00:40:42,232 --> 00:40:44,026
It’s strawberry-flavored scent!

780
00:40:44,901 --> 00:40:45,986
That’s why!

781
00:40:45,986 --> 00:40:47,070
It smells amazing.

782
00:40:49,072 --> 00:40:50,782
Hey! Stop that! Stop that!

783
00:40:50,782 --> 00:40:51,883
What are you doing?!

784
00:40:51,908 --> 00:40:52,770
Eww!

785
00:40:53,076 --> 00:40:53,988
Stop!

786
00:40:54,328 --> 00:40:55,412
You're disgusting! Eww!

787
00:40:55,912 --> 00:40:57,622
You’re mean to me!

788
00:40:57,622 --> 00:41:00,559
What's so gross about smelling
things with my eyes closed?

789
00:41:00,584 --> 00:41:01,590
You're like...

790
00:41:01,793 --> 00:41:02,419
I don't know.

791
00:41:02,419 --> 00:41:03,754
It's a disturbing image!

792
00:41:04,004 --> 00:41:04,796
Ugh!

793
00:41:04,796 --> 00:41:05,605
Stop that!

794
00:41:05,630 --> 00:41:06,523
Your face should be censored!

795
00:41:06,548 --> 00:41:08,133
- Okay! Fine, fine!
- It’s gross, Alys!

796
00:41:08,133 --> 00:41:09,384
I won't close my eyes!

797
00:41:09,384 --> 00:41:10,844
It’ll just be wide-eyed forever!

798
00:41:12,721 --> 00:41:14,306
You'll look insane.

799
00:41:15,674 --> 00:41:17,176
I'm about to go
insane on your ass.

800
00:41:18,185 --> 00:41:18,977
Yeah, whatever.

801
00:41:18,977 --> 00:41:21,021
Just shut up and drive.
You know too much.

802
00:41:21,605 --> 00:41:22,814
Come on, let's go.

803
00:41:34,618 --> 00:41:35,577
So?

804
00:41:35,577 --> 00:41:36,828
What's up?

805
00:41:39,164 --> 00:41:41,083
Keep it coming!

806
00:41:41,598 --> 00:41:43,668
Whoa!

807
00:41:43,668 --> 00:41:45,170
Looks like you’re geared up.

808
00:41:45,879 --> 00:41:47,214
Oh, take it easy!

809
00:41:48,715 --> 00:41:50,133
I really needed that.

810
00:41:51,968 --> 00:41:52,928
Okay.

811
00:41:53,136 --> 00:41:54,262
So, here's the thing.

812
00:41:54,638 --> 00:41:57,224
Drake and Cristine are
getting married, right?

813
00:41:59,434 --> 00:42:00,403
What?!

814
00:42:01,061 --> 00:42:02,229
Don't tell me you didn't know.

815
00:42:02,979 --> 00:42:04,106
That's news to me!

816
00:42:04,439 --> 00:42:05,649
You had no idea?

817
00:42:05,899 --> 00:42:06,650
No!

818
00:42:06,650 --> 00:42:07,567
Married?

819
00:42:07,567 --> 00:42:08,606
- Really?
- Yeah!

820
00:42:08,878 --> 00:42:11,012
They're like tying the
knot in less than a month.

821
00:42:11,738 --> 00:42:12,989
Wait, wait. To who again?

822
00:42:13,848 --> 00:42:15,496
Cristine Ann Stinson.

823
00:42:15,617 --> 00:42:16,493
Ring a bell?

824
00:42:21,706 --> 00:42:23,125
Here's what I know.

825
00:42:23,708 --> 00:42:25,544
So, supposedly,

826
00:42:26,128 --> 00:42:28,964
Cristine was Drake's bestfriend
in their college days

827
00:42:28,964 --> 00:42:31,007
when Shaira went off to migrate.

828
00:42:31,559 --> 00:42:32,685
Go on.

829
00:42:33,165 --> 00:42:34,291
I don't know.

830
00:42:35,262 --> 00:42:36,388
But...

831
00:42:36,847 --> 00:42:38,932
Everybody seems to really like Cristine.

832
00:42:39,766 --> 00:42:41,435
They like her for Drake.

833
00:42:43,645 --> 00:42:44,980
Hold that thought.

834
00:42:44,980 --> 00:42:46,082
Have a shot first.

835
00:42:46,280 --> 00:42:47,239
Cheers!

836
00:42:51,653 --> 00:42:53,363
The real question is...

837
00:42:54,322 --> 00:42:55,740
Do you like her for Drake?

838
00:42:56,324 --> 00:42:57,576
Sure!

839
00:42:58,694 --> 00:42:59,653
Of course!

840
00:43:02,581 --> 00:43:03,926
Drake and I?

841
00:43:04,082 --> 00:43:05,208
We're over.

842
00:43:05,542 --> 00:43:06,543
Come on.

843
00:43:07,961 --> 00:43:10,088
We were probably never meant to be.

844
00:43:10,497 --> 00:43:12,291
Maybe he was meant for Cristine.

845
00:43:12,316 --> 00:43:13,692
Oh my gosh.

846
00:43:13,717 --> 00:43:14,731
Really?!

847
00:43:15,026 --> 00:43:16,098
Alys...

848
00:43:16,330 --> 00:43:17,790
It's true!

849
00:43:17,971 --> 00:43:18,832
Really?

850
00:43:19,055 --> 00:43:21,131
Tofer, I'm 22.

851
00:43:21,156 --> 00:43:22,098
Okay?

852
00:43:22,947 --> 00:43:23,702
Sure,

853
00:43:23,727 --> 00:43:26,731
maybe I was happy with
flirting and thrills back then.

854
00:43:27,898 --> 00:43:28,817
But...

855
00:43:29,107 --> 00:43:30,233
It's different now.

856
00:43:30,650 --> 00:43:32,110
It's so different now.

857
00:43:34,013 --> 00:43:36,354
I want assurance.

858
00:43:36,379 --> 00:43:38,049
I want constant love.

859
00:43:38,074 --> 00:43:39,659
I want consistency.

860
00:43:40,619 --> 00:43:41,953
Do you get me?

861
00:43:41,953 --> 00:43:43,497
Do you understand?

862
00:43:46,146 --> 00:43:47,856
Sure, fine.

863
00:43:47,959 --> 00:43:49,473
You can say that

864
00:43:49,794 --> 00:43:53,173
Drake did make me feel like my heart
was gonna jump out of my chest.

865
00:43:53,173 --> 00:43:55,258
But that was when I was 18 years old.

866
00:43:55,258 --> 00:43:56,246
Come on!

867
00:43:57,469 --> 00:43:59,137
He left me when I was 18.

868
00:43:59,950 --> 00:44:02,828
And now, he wants me back at 22.

869
00:44:03,600 --> 00:44:05,185
That's just not gonna happen.

870
00:44:05,185 --> 00:44:06,478
That's not how it works.

871
00:44:06,978 --> 00:44:08,396
I'm 22 now!

872
00:44:08,980 --> 00:44:10,137
And wiser.

873
00:44:10,565 --> 00:44:14,110
I'm 22 and so freakin' in love

874
00:44:14,313 --> 00:44:16,899
with Tripp Marco Palma.

875
00:44:17,447 --> 00:44:18,887
His cousin.

876
00:44:19,282 --> 00:44:21,343
Well, when you say it like that,
it sounds really weird.

877
00:44:21,368 --> 00:44:22,827
Because it is weird!

878
00:44:22,827 --> 00:44:24,231
No, it's not!

879
00:44:25,372 --> 00:44:26,831
But I gotta give it to you.

880
00:44:26,998 --> 00:44:28,458
Your answer though,

881
00:44:28,726 --> 00:44:30,937
straight out of a beauty pageant, like...

882
00:44:31,459 --> 00:44:33,669
“And I... thank you!”

883
00:44:35,480 --> 00:44:38,528
- You rehearsed that. Didn't you?
- I did not!

884
00:44:38,718 --> 00:44:41,137
For your information,
I can be profound if I want to be.

885
00:44:41,763 --> 00:44:43,098
Profound?

886
00:44:43,123 --> 00:44:44,641
Doesn't suit you.

887
00:44:44,641 --> 00:44:45,392
Shut it!

888
00:44:47,666 --> 00:44:48,792
In all seriousness,

889
00:44:51,022 --> 00:44:52,148
Alys...

890
00:44:53,733 --> 00:44:55,043
Tripp

891
00:44:55,443 --> 00:44:56,861
loves you

892
00:44:56,886 --> 00:44:57,887
very much.

893
00:44:58,178 --> 00:44:59,637
I know that!

894
00:44:59,864 --> 00:45:02,701
Tripp loves me and I can feel it.

895
00:45:03,055 --> 00:45:04,431
Then, good!

896
00:45:05,070 --> 00:45:07,770
So you should know the
consequences of your actions.

897
00:45:08,021 --> 00:45:12,285
And how your decisions
have impact.

898
00:45:13,044 --> 00:45:14,337
Listen.

899
00:45:14,337 --> 00:45:17,653
You'll break him, if you leave him.

900
00:45:18,930 --> 00:45:23,278
But you'll destroy him,
if you leave him for Drake!

901
00:45:25,486 --> 00:45:26,779
Do you get that?

902
00:45:49,956 --> 00:45:51,393
I know.

903
00:45:53,376 --> 00:45:54,636
I know.

904
00:45:55,337 --> 00:45:56,546
Okay.

905
00:45:56,546 --> 00:45:57,690
So?

906
00:45:58,133 --> 00:45:59,987
Are you leaving Tripp for Drake?

907
00:47:15,500 --> 00:47:16,751
What the heck?!

908
00:47:17,003 --> 00:47:19,005
It’s so early to ruin my day.

909
00:47:20,492 --> 00:47:21,910
What time is it?

910
00:47:24,521 --> 00:47:26,231
Oh no, I'm late for the meeting!

911
00:47:32,025 --> 00:47:33,192
Ouch!

912
00:47:33,474 --> 00:47:34,516
My god.

913
00:47:37,105 --> 00:47:38,732
My head hurts!

914
00:47:39,858 --> 00:47:41,234
Damn that Tofer!

915
00:47:41,234 --> 00:47:43,319
He got me completely drunk!

916
00:47:46,072 --> 00:47:48,158
Should I call in sick today?

917
00:47:49,367 --> 00:47:51,453
I mean I do feel sick.

918
00:47:55,143 --> 00:47:56,228
No, Alys!

919
00:47:56,395 --> 00:47:58,146
Let’s be professional.

920
00:47:59,210 --> 00:48:00,545
We can't lose like this!

921
00:48:04,841 --> 00:48:07,594
I'm on the way.

922
00:48:09,352 --> 00:48:11,354
You have five minutes, Alys.

923
00:48:12,265 --> 00:48:15,018
One... two... three!

924
00:48:17,937 --> 00:48:19,773
I said I'm on my way!

925
00:48:45,215 --> 00:48:47,415
Please coordinate with Drake instead.

926
00:48:48,176 --> 00:48:49,594
Thanks a lot, Alys.

927
00:48:49,594 --> 00:48:51,141
And I really have to go now.

928
00:48:51,387 --> 00:48:52,376
Bye!

929
00:49:02,440 --> 00:49:03,775
You're really leaving?

930
00:49:05,360 --> 00:49:06,277
Yes.

931
00:49:06,903 --> 00:49:08,352
It was scheduled a long time ago.

932
00:49:08,696 --> 00:49:09,531
I mean,

933
00:49:09,531 --> 00:49:11,324
even before the wedding preps.

934
00:49:11,574 --> 00:49:13,535
This convention is already set.

935
00:49:14,953 --> 00:49:16,496
Can't you still cancel it?

936
00:49:17,372 --> 00:49:18,579
No way.

937
00:49:19,290 --> 00:49:23,336
And I already told Alys to coordinate
with you on the wedding.

938
00:49:25,004 --> 00:49:26,352
So behave, Drake.

939
00:49:27,144 --> 00:49:28,187
Please.

940
00:49:29,165 --> 00:49:30,666
Are you really sure?

941
00:49:32,473 --> 00:49:35,415
That sad boy routine
won't work on me.

942
00:49:36,212 --> 00:49:39,657
I'm already stressing making
the perfect wedding happen!

943
00:49:39,821 --> 00:49:42,501
Would you let me,
at least, enjoy Paris first?

944
00:49:45,149 --> 00:49:47,318
Look, I really have to go now.

945
00:49:47,318 --> 00:49:48,313
Okay?

946
00:49:49,696 --> 00:49:50,696
Bye now.

947
00:50:05,628 --> 00:50:06,921
<i>Cristine's gone.</i>

948
00:50:06,921 --> 00:50:09,090
<i>It's you and me again, Alys.</i>

949
00:50:09,382 --> 00:50:10,800
<i>Hello, pseudo bride.</i>

950
00:50:11,092 --> 00:50:12,510
<i>Make your groom happy.</i>

951
00:50:12,510 --> 00:50:13,636
<i>You ready?</i>

952
00:50:25,356 --> 00:50:28,710
<i>On the next episode of</i>
<i>Dating Alys Perez. </i>

953
00:50:28,735 --> 00:50:29,766
No, thanks.

954
00:50:29,868 --> 00:50:31,563
Good morning to you, too, Alys.

955
00:50:31,588 --> 00:50:32,506
Come on.

956
00:50:32,975 --> 00:50:34,893
Cristine and I aren't even the same size.

957
00:50:35,246 --> 00:50:36,956
So you're telling me that

958
00:50:36,981 --> 00:50:38,071
you're fat?

959
00:50:39,185 --> 00:50:40,311
Excuse me?!

960
00:50:40,361 --> 00:50:42,329
Ms. Alys, the gown might get ruined.

961
00:50:42,916 --> 00:50:44,000
Shut up!

962
00:50:44,208 --> 00:50:45,710
On the count of three,
you're gonna zip it up.

963
00:50:45,710 --> 00:50:48,243
I don't care if it splits.
You're going to do it!

964
00:50:48,755 --> 00:50:50,340
Why would you agree

965
00:50:50,340 --> 00:50:53,051
to be wedding planner
for your own ex?

966
00:50:53,051 --> 00:50:54,071
Right?

967
00:50:54,275 --> 00:50:56,778
Same old Alys.

968
00:50:57,472 --> 00:50:58,423
So?

969
00:50:59,766 --> 00:51:01,351
Where’s our next destination?

970
00:51:03,394 --> 00:51:04,646
What are you doing here?

971
00:51:04,646 --> 00:51:06,564
I'm here to pick up Ms. Stinson's gown.

972
00:51:06,564 --> 00:51:08,041
I'm taking it to Batangas.

973
00:51:08,066 --> 00:51:10,430
You'll forever be a martyr.

974
00:51:14,113 --> 00:51:15,615
Can you feel it, Alys?

975
00:51:17,200 --> 00:51:18,534
Can you feel it?

976
00:51:19,574 --> 00:51:22,702
That's the heart of a man
who's obsessed with you.

